BENIN – A chieftain of the People’s Democratic Party (PDP) and former candidate in Oredo federal constituency, Omo Osagie Efosa, has enjoined Christian faithful in Edo State and Nigeria in general to be tolerant and abide to the virtues of the peaceful dispo­sition of Jesus Christ whose birth the entire world has just celebrated. Omo Osagie, who spoke to journalists in Benin, not­ed that this year’s celebra­tion came at a time when the world was and still com­bating the resurgence of the Coronavirus pandemic. He also said that besides COVID-19, Nigeria still faced security and economic chal­lenges which, he expressed optimism that sooner Nigeria would come out and Oredo people would have cause to smile once again. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! He, however, praised God and expressed happiness that the resilience and positive at­titudes of Nigerians did not stop the country from pre­vailing against the challeng­es but also ensured that their strains did not stop responsi­ble celebration of Christmas, just as they look forward to a peaceful celebration of the New Year in the state and Ni­geria at large. SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION